==English==

===Etymology===
First attested in 1521. {{bor|en|fr|abstention}}, from {{der|en|LL.|abstēntiō}} from {{der|en|la|abstinēō||withhold, to abstain}}

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|RP}} {{IPA|/əbˈstɛn.ʃn̩/|lang=en}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/æbˈstɛn.ʃn̩/|/əbˈstɛn.ʃn̩/|/æbˈstɛn.t͡ʃn̩/|/əbˈstɛn.t͡ʃn̩/|lang=en}}
* {{audio|en-us-abstention.ogg|Audio (US)|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{lb|en|obsolete}} The act of restraining oneself. {{defdate|Attested from the early 16<sup>th</sup> century until the med 17<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED>{{R:SOED5|page=9}}</ref>
# The act of [[abstaining]]; a holding [[aloof]]; refraining from. {{defdate|First attested in the early 17<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
# The act of declining to vote on a particular issue. {{defdate|First attested in the late 19<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
# [[Non-participation]] in the [[political]] [[world]]; as a [[country]] avoiding [[international]] [[affairs]].

